trans-unit.source: Use Azure Data Factory with SQL Data Warehouse
trans-unit.target: Use Azure Data Factory with SQL Data Warehouse

trans-unit.source: Azure Data Factory provides a fully managed method for orchestrating the transfer of data and execution of stored procedures on SQL Data Warehouse.
trans-unit.target: Azure Data Factory provides a fully managed method for orchestrating the transfer of data and execution of stored procedures on SQL Data Warehouse.

trans-unit.source: This will allow you to more easily set-up and schedule complex Extract Transform and Load (ETL) procedures with SQL Data Warehouse.
trans-unit.target: This will allow you to more easily set-up and schedule complex Extract Transform and Load (ETL) procedures with SQL Data Warehouse.

trans-unit.source: For a more complete overview of Azure Data Factory, see the <link><linkText>Azure Data Factory documentation[]</linkText><title></title></link>.
trans-unit.target: For a more complete overview of Azure Data Factory, see the <link><linkText>Azure Data Factory documentation[]</linkText><title></title></link>.

trans-unit.source: Data Movement
trans-unit.target: Data Movement

trans-unit.source: Azure Data Factory enables data movement between both on-premises sources and different Azure services.
trans-unit.target: Azure Data Factory enables data movement between both on-premises sources and different Azure services.

trans-unit.source: Overall, current integration with Azure Data Factory supports data movement to and from the following locations:
trans-unit.target: Overall, current integration with Azure Data Factory supports data movement to and from the following locations:

trans-unit.source: Azure blob storage
trans-unit.target: Azure blob storage

trans-unit.source: Azure SQL Database
trans-unit.target: Azure SQL Database

trans-unit.source: On-premises SQL Server
trans-unit.target: On-premises SQL Server

trans-unit.source: SQL Server on IaaS
trans-unit.target: SQL Server on IaaS

trans-unit.source: For information on how to set up a data copy activity see <link><linkText>Copy data with Azure Data Factory[]</linkText><title></title></link>.
trans-unit.target: For information on how to set up a data copy activity see <link><linkText>Copy data with Azure Data Factory[]</linkText><title></title></link>.

trans-unit.source: At this time Azure Data Factory cannot be used to transfer data into non-nullable columns in SQL Data Warehouse.
trans-unit.target: At this time Azure Data Factory cannot be used to transfer data into non-nullable columns in SQL Data Warehouse.

trans-unit.source: Stored Procedures
trans-unit.target: Stored Procedures

trans-unit.source: In the same way it can be used to schedule data transfer, Azure Data Factory can also be used to orchestrate the execution of stored procedures.
trans-unit.target: In the same way it can be used to schedule data transfer, Azure Data Factory can also be used to orchestrate the execution of stored procedures.

trans-unit.source: This allows more complex pipelines to be created and extends Azure Data Factory's ability to leverage the computational power of SQL Data Warehouse.
trans-unit.target: This allows more complex pipelines to be created and extends Azure Data Factory's ability to leverage the computational power of SQL Data Warehouse.
